        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 17 at 4:42PM CDT by NWS Amarillo TX</headline>
        <description>At 442 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 10
miles northwest of Lora, or 11 miles north of Miami, moving north at
15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Miami and Lora.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
